\begin_layout Plain Layout
Replication of a scientific study (computational or other) means repeating
 a published protocol, respecting its spirit and intentions but varying
 the technical details.
 For computational work, this would mean using different software, running
 a simulation from different initial conditions, etc.
 The idea is to change something that everyone believes shouldn’t matter,
 and see if the scientific conclusions are affected or not.
